        Constructor for the Two Server System
        Parameters:
        hexpLambdaOne - Rate for first exponential in hyperexponential
        hexpLambdaTwo - Rate for second exponential in hyperexponential
        hexpP - The probability for the hyperexponential
        expLambda - The inter-arrival rate of jobs

    • Method Detail

      • generateJob

        public void generateJob​(boolean coinFlip)
        Generates a job and places it in the system. It will either pick a random server to place it on (coinflip), or the queue with the least amount of jobs, depending on the boolean passed in.
        Parameters:
        coinFlip - Whether or not to do a coinflip for sending the job to a server

      • runSimulation

        public int runSimulation​(boolean coinFlip)
        Runs the simulation.
        Parameters:
        coinFlip - Policy for sending jobs to which servers. (See generateJob() for more informatio)
        Returns:
        The average number of jobs in the system during the system.
